<p>In the latest development, Sudan’s military said it withdrew from El-Fasher in Darfur and the paramilitary Rapid Support Forces (RSF) have taken control of the army’s last base in the city, a decisive shift in control of the region . The change follows an 18-month siege of El-Fasher and raises fears that hundreds of thousands of civilians trapped inside face worsening shortages and danger . United Nations officials and rights groups warned the risk of ethnically motivated atrocities is rising after reports of dozens of civilians killed and allegations of summary executions .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/BubEyWN_yCmlJCaylxf6qDQBNiJjC3oNh6khOejV5Q6u11lNWyVsEivJfIXTYeR51i1_U0GT3RrIVbR-AVb6VfWiFHqAq7bAR1YJ2eHUpl7BbNmiZxOsH3suaj_VtSny77FLezyv8K-mLIU2IdES4nbpFYeFIwv4LFtHPF0YezEJkXF_Hrr0NQ' alt='A shelter in El Fasher, Sudan, where displaced people protected themselves from shelling this month; the military said it had withdrawn from the city.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Political split: Analysts say the RSF takeover could deepen a geographic division between rival military factions, entrenching separate control zones across Sudan</li><li>Civilian toll: Civilians in El-Fasher have sheltered from air strikes, drone activity and shelling while hunger and shortages have worsened during the prolonged siege</li><li>UN findings: The UN rights office reported allegations of summary executions and warned the likelihood of ethnically motivated violations is growing after the RSF claimed control</li><li>Past context: Rights groups note the RSF grew out of Janjaweed militias linked to earlier campaigns in Darfur, and cite past mass killings as a source of alarm now</li></ul><blockquote>Extremely precarious situation - UN rights chief</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Sudan military (Gen. Abdel Fattah al-Burhan): Military officers decided to withdraw from the city entirely in hopes of sparing the civilian population from further violence. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/28/world/africa/sudan-el-fasher-burhan-rsf.html'>New York Times</a>)</li><li>Rapid Support Forces (RSF): RSF claimed it had seized the army&#x27;s last base in El-Fasher and released footage showing fighters in the streets. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/nx-s1-5587665/el-fasher-darfur-sudan-genocide'>NPR / Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Medical NGOs and rights groups (MSF, Refugees International): Medical groups urged that civilians be allowed to flee and warned that ethnically targeted killings could occur again in El-Fasher. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/ngos-warn-genocide-sudan-amid-rsfs-el-fasher-takeover'>The New Arab</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/nx-s1-5587665/el-fasher-darfur-sudan-genocide'>&#x27;Trapped and terrified&#x27;: warnings as Sudanese militia advance on Darfur city</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/sudan-army-admits-loss-el-fasher-amid-reports-atrocities'>Sudan army admits loss of El-Fasher amid reports of atrocities</a> - newarab.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/28/world/africa/sudan-el-fasher-burhan-rsf.html'>Sudan’s Military Withdraws From El Fasher in Darfur, Handing City to R.S.F.</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/27/sudan-s-paramilitary-forces-seize-el-fasher-army-s-last-darfur-stronghold_6746832_4.html'>Sudan&#x27;s paramilitary forces seize El-Fasher, army&#x27;s last Darfur stronghold</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/video-sudan-forces-capture-of-el-fasher-may-worsen-division/'>Sudan force&#x27;s capture of El Fasher may worsen division</a> - theglobeandmail.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/28/sudan-army-announces-withdrawal-from-el-fasher-un-warns-of-rsf-atrocities'>Sudan army withdraws from Darfur’s el-Fasher, UN warns of RSF atrocities</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/Sudanese-forces-capture-of-Darfur-city-could-entrench-countrys-split'>Sudanese force&#x27;s capture of Darfur city could entrench country&#x27;s split</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/tv-shows/eye-on-africa/20251027-sudan-s-rsf-overrun-the-army-s-last-stronghold-in-the-darfur-region'>Sudan&#x27;s RSF paramilitaries overrun army&#x27;s last stronghold in Darfur region</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510280008.html'>Sudan: UN Warns of Ethnically Motivated &#x27;Atrocities&#x27; in Sudan&#x27;s El-Fasher</a> - allafrica.com</li></ul>